Anonymous Tue 10 May 2022 13:59:31 No.47610656 Report
Quoted By: >>47610670 >>47628078
>>47610579
your brain isn't globally multithreaded like a modern CPU.
you already have systems in your subconscious that work on problems while you're not thinking about them.
All a 'tulpa' does is clutter up your ability to think straight, since you're creating a character which your brain has to switch to and focus all it's mental processes through, and then switch back to you to analyze the mess it made.
And if you've made yourself delusional enough, you'll start to believe that this figment is real, when it's nothing more than a crude emulation of a person helped made feel real by your mirror neurons.

tl;dr don't do it, it's bad for you
